<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Secretary of State to the
                            Embassy in China</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v10</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1056</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1056</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-06-06T17:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-06-06T17:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-06T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="1056" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1056">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.8571/6–346</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in China</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-06T18:00:00-04:00">June 6, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>247. Satisfactory await reply Chinese Govt to representations already made on
                    exemption agencies and officials US Govt from taxes. Urtel 908 June 3. Keep Dept
                        informed.<note n="9" xml:id="d1056fn9">A reply from the Chinese Foreign
                        Office, dated August 10, referred only to the income tax on lease of
                        property and said exemption could not be granted as tax was on the lessor of
                        the property (Nanking Embassy file 851.2 Shanghai house tax).</note>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Shanghai as Deptel 1003.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
